Incidents.Name: Honeydew and Canoe Fires
Incidents.Location: King Range, 14 miles north and 15 miles west of Garberville
Incidents.ConditionStatement:
There is a significant risk to firefighters as large trees within the Canoe Fire are falling over as the fire weakens their root system.
The Canoe Fire is approximately 95% contained.
The Honeydew Fire is 98% contained.
Resource demobilization is in progress.
Responsibility for the fire will transition from Incident Command Team #5 to the CDF Humboldt-Del Norte Unit at 7a.m. today.
Incidents.SearchDescription: The Honeydew and Canoe Fires took place in the CDF Humboldt-Del Norte Unit between September 3 and October 6 2003, burning 11,861 acres on the Honeydew Fire and 10,253 on the Canoe Fire.
Incidents.SearchKeywords: Honeydew, Canoe, September and October 2003, Humboldt, Del Norte, Lightning, King, Garberville
